'''Anjumani-shuara''' (Persian - "Poets council") was a literary council of the 19th century in [[Azerbaijan]].
It was first held by Sheykhali khan Kangarli in 1831 in [[Ordubad]]. From 1870-80 the council was led by Haji agha Fagir Ordubadi. Later this mission was obliged to Mohammad Taghi Sidgi. The council’s activity operated with different intervals and there were lots of well-known writers and poets. After the death of Fagir and shifting of Sidgi in [[Nakhchivan (city)|Nakhchivan]] the council was weakened and suspended its activities in 1890-1895.<ref>http://azerbaijans.com/content_1787_en.html</ref>

