The '''artist's [[CD-ROM]]''' and [[DVD-ROM]] are new forms of the [[Artist's book]]. Presentation of work in this format enables artists to put [[multimedia]] and [[Hypertext]] into [[Installation art]].  Pioneers of the new format include [[Laurie Anderson]], [[Jean-Jacques Birgé]], [[David Blair (director)|David Blair]], [[John Maeda]], [[Christine Tamblyn]], [[Marita Liulia]], [[Marjorie Franklin]], [[Paul Tompkins (artist)|Paul Tompkins]], [[Elizabeth Hinkle-Turner]], [[Takahiko Iimura]] and [[Rodrigo Toledo]].

==Notable examples==

*''Puppet Motel'' by [[Laurie Anderson]] and [[Hsin-Chien Huang]]
*[[Waxweb]] by [[David Blair (director)|David Blair]]
*[[Reactive Books]] by [[John Maeda]]
*''Machiavel'' by [[Jean-Jacques Birgé]] and [[Antoine Schmitt]]
*[[The Ambitious Bitch]] by [[Marita Liulia]]
*[[Machines à écrire]] by Antoine Denize
*[[Xplora]] and [[Eve]] by [[Peter Gabriel]] and Michael Coulson


