{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}} {{Use British English|date=April 2015}} {{Infobox street | name = FACT | image = FACT Liverpool.JPG | caption = Exterior of FACT | postal_code = [[L postcode area|L1 4DQ]] | location = [[Liverpool]] |website = {{url|www.fact.co.uk}} }}
'''FACT''' ('''Foundation for Art & Creative Technology''') is a [[new media art]]s centre based on ''Wood Street'' in [[Liverpool]], [[England]]. FACT hosts art projects and exhibitions as well as being a cinema.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/whats-on/whats-on-news/liverpools-arts-hub-cinema-fact-8488181 |title= Liverpool's arts hub and cinema FACT reveal 2015 programme and exhibitions |date= 21 January 2015 |accessdate= 1 January 2016 |work= Liverpool Echo |author= Peter Guy}}</ref>
==History== FACT was Liverpool's first purpose-built arts centre for more than 60 years. It was opened in February 2003 by its founding executive director Eddie Berg, having cost £10 million to build. The building is linked to [[Bold Street]], one of Liverpool's main shopping areas, by a public square off Wood Street and Colquitt Street.
==Events== The cinema hosted a Question and Answer session with [[Quentin Tarantino]] in 2007 for the UK release of ''[[Death Proof]].''<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.bbc.co.uk/liverpool/content/articles/2007/09/12/tarantino_review_feature.shtml |title= Tarantino in Liverpool |work= BBC News |author= Peter Argyle |date= 12 September 2007 |accessdate= 1 January 2016}}</ref> In 2015 FACT hosted an art event in which [[Shia LaBeouf]] answered phone calls from the public.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-35059685 |title= Shia LaBeouf takes public calls in Liverpool art gallery |date= 16 December 2015 |accessdate= 1 January 2016 |work= BBC News}}</ref> On March 22, 2017, FACT became the location of [[LaBeouf, Rönkkö & Turner]]'s He Will Not Divide Us project.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.fact.co.uk/news-articles/2017/03/hewillnotdivideus.aspx |title=HEWILLNOTDIVIDE.US |work=FACT News |date= 21 March 2017 |accessdate= 22 March 2017}}</ref>
== The building == Designed by architectural firm [[Austin-Smith:Lord]], the building is situated on ''Wood Street'' in the Ropewalks area of the city centre.<ref>http://www.fact.co.uk/main/visit/building/?group=4&parent=28&link_id=28</ref> It contains three gallery spaces, four cinema screens and a multimedia suite and also comprises a cafe, a bar and a lounge area.
